<font color="#FF0000">SERENE TIME</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep 25 23:03:16 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art,<br><br>
The strange sensation is the feeling you have when you think you have been dealt a killing blow.<br><br>
The concussion so heavy I was thrown through the air.  No sound just silence.  A momentary flash of crimson and a burning sensation in my eyes.  The burning was the blood flowing from my head down my face.  Only thought was I lost my face.  AT a time like this I was worried about being scarred.  Never cared what happened or why.<br><br>
No fear, anger, or rage.  Just a serene feeling.  All the way to the surgeons table was nothing.  Shock possibly, will never know.<br><br>
Funny, but I never realized until now I shut most of the sensation out.  Driving force was I am a pilot, don't lose consciousness or they'll ground your ass.  Nothing else mattered.
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


